# tests/tsan.supp — ThreadSanitizer suppressions
#
# Intentionally empty in M0. DPDK-internal synchronization primitives
# (rte_rwlock, rte_mcslock, rte_rcu_qsbr) will trigger TSan reports
# once we actually invoke them — see harness.md §H5.2. Populated
# starting M3+ when EAL comes up on worker lcores. Only DPDK-internal
# symbols are permitted in here; any pktgate-owned code that TSan
# flags is a real bug, not a suppression target.

# M3 C1: DPDK mempool allocator internal — rte_eal_mp_wait_lcore()
# synchronizes the worker→main join, but DPDK's malloc_elem_free
# (called from rte_mempool_free) triggers a race because the internal
# memory-region metadata was read by the worker's rte_eth_rx_burst
# within DPDK's own lock-free paths. The memset inside malloc_elem_free
# is not annotated with TSAN annotations in DPDK 25.11.
race:malloc_elem_free
